{"title": "Anonymous Benefactor", "content": "Oh, woe is The Pollyanna! Her humble aspirations are practically a Tragic Dream because she's poor / an orphan / meant to suffer at the whims of the cosmos. But what's this? She wakes up one morning to discover the exact thing she wanted / needed at the foot of her bed!\n\nMethod of delivery may vary, but this gift is the hallmark of the Anonymous Benefactor, someone whose \"altruistic\" motives and identity are a mystery. Usually it's someone who knows her (or him) and wants to help her while maintaining anonymity. This may be because they: would rather not lose their Jerkass reputation by revealing their good nature, want to avoid breaking some stuffy officious rule by showing favoritism, or to avoid getting caught by the authorities if they're a fugitive.\n\nOf course, not all gifts are ultimately good, and some may herald incredible changes to the recipient. If the gift is the Sword of Plot Advancement given to the The Chosen One, it signals the start of their adventure\u2014 whether they want to go or not.\n\nOf course, the Anonymous Benefactor might have less altruistic motives and send a Trojan Horse with the intent to harm her, or as a means to ensure the hero gets the MacGuffin so they can steal it. Other possibilities include the Anonymous Benefactor helping a minor villain or non-evil rival to the heroine. In which case this is usually a ploy by the Big Bad to give the hero someone else to chew on while their own Evil Plan advances.\n\nUsually their identity is discovered or revealed at the end of the story, at least by the viewer. More often than not, it's a parent, sibling, or someone the heroine helped long ago. A good many characters may decide not to look this gift horse in the mouth despite having known enemies.\n\nSee also Help Yourself in the Future and Unexpected Inheritance. Related to the Mysterious Employer, where the benefactor offers the character in question steady work, at the cost of not asking too many questions. Compare Mysterious Backer.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnonymousBenefactor?from=Main.MysteriousBenefactor", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MagicalGirlLyricalNanohaAs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MagicalGirlLyricalNanohaAs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MagicalGirlLyricalNanohaStrikers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MaiOtome", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/BestStudentCouncil", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/GlassMask", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MyDaddyLongLegs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SpiderMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/ArchieComics", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/DisneyDucksComicUniverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/EZMoney", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TerminatorGenisys", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/NowYouSeeMe", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheCountOfMonteCristo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/GreatExpectations", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HarryPotterAndTheGobletOfFire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ALittlePrincess", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/TamoraPierce", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ProtectorOfTheSmall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SongOfTheLioness", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DaddyLongLegs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheMysteriousIsland", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/GreekNinja", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DoctorWhoExpandedUniverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TimeLordFairyTales", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheMarkAndTheVoid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MASH", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheJeffersons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Bones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Glee", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CSINY", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/CrimeStory", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ThirtyRock", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/SirArthurConanDoylesTheLostWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/PersonOfInterest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HalfLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HalfLife2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MassEffect2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/